text: Rhoda Mulaudzi (born 2 December 1989) is a South African footballer who plays as a forward for Dinamo Minsk and the South Africa women's national team. ==Club career== On 20 August 2018, Canberra United announced they had signed Mulaudzi for the 2018–19 W-League Season. She joined the club alongside fellow South African Refiloe Jane; they are the first players from South Africa to play in the W-League. ==International career== Mulaudzi made her senior debut for South Africa during the 2015 African Games on 7 September that year in a 1–1 draw against Cameroon. ==References== Category:1989 births Category:Living people Category:South African Venda people Category:Sportspeople from Soweto Category:South African women's soccer players Category:Women's association football forwards Category:Mamelodi Sundowns F.C. players Category:W-League (Australia) players Category:Canberra United FC players Category:South Africa women's international soccer players Category:Footballers at the 2012 Summer Olympics Category:Footballers at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic soccer players of South Africa Category:South African expatriate soccer players Category:South African expatriate sportspeople in Australia Category:Expatriate women's soccer players in Australia Category:2019 FIFA Women's World Cup players Category:Apollon Ladies F.C. players
